1
00:00:01,500 --> 00:00:04,572
Dante is thirty-five years old.

2
00:00:05,372 --> 00:00:08,276
He is in the middle of his life.

3
00:00:09,076 --> 00:00:12,868
One day, he wakes up in a forest.

4
00:00:13,668 --> 00:00:16,284
The forest is dark.

5
00:00:17,084 --> 00:00:19,100
He is afraid.

6
00:00:19,900 --> 00:00:22,180
He does not know where he is.

7
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:26,268
He does not remember how he got here.

8
00:00:27,068 --> 00:00:30,356
"Where am I?" says Dante.

9
00:00:31,156 --> 00:00:34,852
He looks up and sees a mountain.

10
00:00:35,652 --> 00:00:38,628
The sun shines on the top.

11
00:00:39,428 --> 00:00:43,556
"I must climb that mountain," thinks Dante.

12
00:00:44,356 --> 00:00:48,076
He starts to walk toward the mountain.

13
00:00:48,876 --> 00:00:52,236
But an animal blocks the road.

14
00:00:53,036 --> 00:00:58,148
It is a leopard. A big wild cat.

15
00:00:58,948 --> 00:01:02,500
The leopard is fast and dangerous.

16
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:07,044
Dante is afraid but keeps walking.

17
00:01:07,844 --> 00:01:10,364
Then he sees a lion.

18
00:01:11,164 --> 00:01:14,188
The lion is big and strong.

19
00:01:14,988 --> 00:01:18,012
It raises its head and roars.

20
00:01:18,812 --> 00:01:21,044
Dante trembles.

21
00:01:21,844 --> 00:01:24,532
Then a she-wolf arrives.

22
00:01:25,332 --> 00:01:28,428
The she-wolf is thin and hungry.

23
00:01:29,228 --> 00:01:32,324
Her eyes are terrible.

24
00:01:33,124 --> 00:01:36,268
Dante cannot go forward.

25
00:01:37,068 --> 00:01:39,876
He goes back into the dark forest.

26
00:01:40,676 --> 00:01:43,844
"I am lost," says Dante.

27
00:01:44,644 --> 00:01:47,332
But then he sees a man.

28
00:01:48,132 --> 00:01:51,084
"Who are you?" asks Dante.

29
00:01:51,884 --> 00:01:55,316
"I am Virgil," says the man.

30
00:01:56,116 --> 00:02:01,300
"I am a poet. I died a long time ago."

31
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:05,628
"Why are you here?" asks Dante.

32
00:02:06,428 --> 00:02:12,020
"A woman sent me. Her name is Beatrice."

33
00:02:12,820 --> 00:02:18,196
"Beatrice!" says Dante. "My love!"

34
00:02:18,996 --> 00:02:23,316
"Beatrice watches you from heaven," says Virgil.

35
00:02:24,116 --> 00:02:26,468
"She is afraid for you."

36
00:02:27,268 --> 00:02:31,036
"You must come with me," says Virgil.

37
00:02:31,836 --> 00:02:35,268
"There is another road to the mountain."

38
00:02:36,068 --> 00:02:39,812
"But first we must pass through Hell."

39
00:02:40,612 --> 00:02:45,796
"Hell?" says Dante. "I am afraid."

40
00:02:46,596 --> 00:02:52,428
"Do not be afraid," says Virgil. "I am with you."

41
00:02:53,228 --> 00:02:56,372
They walk together in the forest.

42
00:02:57,172 --> 00:03:00,820
They arrive in front of a great gate.

43
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:04,308
On the gate it is written:

44
00:03:05,108 --> 00:03:09,260
"Abandon all hope, you who enter."

45
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:12,724
Dante reads and trembles.

46
00:03:13,524 --> 00:03:16,596
"Courage," says Virgil.

47
00:03:17,396 --> 00:03:20,852
Virgil takes Dante's hand.

48
00:03:21,652 --> 00:03:24,748
They enter through the gate together.

49
00:03:25,548 --> 00:03:28,836
The journey through Hell begins.
